Even when using an open sprint, 
{code}
POST https:{instanceurl}/rest/agile/1.0/sprint/{sprintId}/issue/{issueId}
{code}
call always returns:
{code}
<status-code>404</status-code>
{code}

And the issue is not added to the sprint.

_Tested with JIRA Agile v6.7.9-D20150721T124923_

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-12227].
  {panel}

All JIRA is set for time format HH:mm, but when you have a window opened for starting a sprint the end date is automatically picked in h:mm a

In JIRA Agile, for scrum board when the plan mode is breaching the max viewable issues number. This error message will appear:
{code}
Maximum number of viewable issues (500) exceeded for this board.
{code}

However in the control chart itself it will only show the following message which is not meaningful at all:
{code}
"This chart cannot be displayed, There are either no issues on this board, or all the issues have been filtered out by the chart refinements."
{code}

The reason control chart is showing the above message is due to plan mode is breaching the max viewable issues number. Therefore it would be best if it could generate a more meaningful error message or display the same warning message in the control chart section.
